<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Cicindela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyperborea">Cicindela hyperborea</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1863c: 1. Type locality: &quot;Methy Portage [= Portage La Loche, northern Saskatchewan], 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hudsonâ€™s">Hudson's</normalizedToken>
Bay Territory&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) in MCZ [# 16]. Note. Methy(e) Portage was the longest portage in the regular fur trade. It lies between Lac La Loche (the top of the Churchill River system) on the southeast and the Clearwater River, which flows into the Athabasca River, on the northwest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="255" pageNumber="256" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="255" pageNumber="256">
<pageBreakToken pageId="255" pageNumber="256" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="255" pageNumber="256">This subspecies, the &quot;Hyperboreal Tiger Beetle&quot;, ranges from southern Northwest Territories to east-central Alberta, central Saskatchewan, west-central Manitoba [see Johnson 1991: Fig. 22] and northeastern Manitoba (Woodcock et al. 2011: 118).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
